<!-- agent-io-safety:begin -->
## Shell and text I/O safety

Before the first risky shell/text boundary—user-controlled or non-ASCII data, complex quoting, structured text, remote commands, secrets, encoding, BOM, line endings, or suspicious terminal display—read and follow [the central rule]({{RULE_PATH}}). On Windows/PowerShell, read it with `node "{{READ_TEXT_PATH}}" "{{RULE_FILE_PATH}}"`, not `Get-Content` or inline OutputEncoding fixes. Routine structured reads and patch/editor operations do not require loading the rule. After one quoting or mojibake failure, use its deterministic helper route.
<!-- agent-io-safety:end -->
